  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of disguising the origin of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. The specific legal definition can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Making the funds appear legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by country, but most follow similar core principles outlined in international anti-money laundering (AML) regulations.",
